The paper discusses recommender systems and their performance limitations due to sparsity of rating data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of social tagging systems to improve recommendation accuracy, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The proposed model involves matrix factorization and collaborative filtering, which are common techniques in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with data sparsity, which is a common issue in the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the use of weighted diffusion on tripartite graphs suggests that the paper could also belong to the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category.
